tafsir[14]{c,v,t}:
  74,1,"O you who is covered with his clothes (this refers to the Prophet (peace be upon him)"
  74,2,"Arise and warn of Allah’s punishment."
  74,3,"Declare the greatness of your Lord."
  74,4,"Purify yourself from sins and your clothes from impurities."
  74,5,"Keep away from the worship of idols."
  74,6,"Do not think that you have done a favour to your Lord by regarding your righteous actions to be plenty."
  74,7,"Be patient for Allah’s sake over the harm that you incur."
  74,8,"When the trumpet will be blown a second time."
  74,9,"That day will be a severe day."
  74,10,"For those who reject Allah and His messengers it will not be easy."
  74,12,"I gave him plenty wealth."
  74,15,"Then despite his denial of Me he desires that I give him more after I gave him all of that."
  74,16,"The matter is not as he thinks. He was opposed to My verses that I revealed to My messenger denying them."
  74,17,"I will impose on him difficulty from a punishment that he will not be able to bear."